WAVE OF ACTION MAIN PAGE: https://www.facebook.com/pages/Worldwide-Wave-of-Action/176294759231015

On April 4th, we will launch the first phase of the Worldwide Wave of Action by gathering at Federal Plaza, and at old Occupy sites around the world, to honor the legacy of Dr. Martin Luther King, Jr. At 6.05 PM CT, the time of his assassination, we will host a vigil ceremony in solidarity with protesters around the world, and resurrect his spirit of nonviolent direct action.

We will also be holding two marches on this day, starting and ending at the Federal Plaza. The first one will depart that location at 12:00 PM. The second will depart at 3:00 PM. If you would rather stay at Federal Plaza than march with us, fliers will be provided for you to pass out if you have not brought your own.

People with opinions across the political spectrum are invited to unite and find common ground against corruption. We will overcome the petty divide created by more or less meaningless party lines and conquer propaganda by forming communities of support and compassion. Together we will begin a sustained fight for freedom and begin engaging in a relentless campaign of nonviolent civil disobedience. People will pledge to take part in whatever tactics they are interested in throughout a sustained three-month cycle. Here are some examples of these tactics:

	>Mass gatherings, demonstrations;
	>Marches, Parades;
	>Flash mobs, swarms;
	>Worker Strikes;
	>Hunger Strikes;
	>Sit-ins;

A more complete list of tactics is available on the description of the worldwide event: https://waveofaction.org/job/worldwide-wave-launch-gatherings/

We MUST come together and unite if we hope to enact any real change. You know what you can do to help make this happen, DO IT!! If we can all come together as a species and act as one I have no doubt this movement will succeed.
